snippet.textDisplay:
You don't require 17 fuckin minutes to break down one of the most easy fights to predict in the history of that division. A 35 yo fighter (who has the mileage of a 45 yo) who is 4-4 in his last 8 (and worse past that) and has never even fought for the belt loses to a dude straight off fuckin vacation who is still in his prime and is a 2-division champ.


What is this ham-fisted nonsense? LMFAO 17 minutes? DID NOT WATCH.


Thank god I skipped this nonsense fight, ignored Dana White's desperate attempts to coddle and over-promote Cerrone all in the sake of publicity and roping in bandwagoning sheeple, and caught it a day later. I even dreamt, literally, that this was a KO victory within a minute. Not braggin; that's just the truth kiddos. And to my eyes, this bout looked fixed. Cerrone's body language in there was ODD to say the least.


What a sad state of affairs in MMA when this outcome is big news.
